OL,3,CHow will no-jury trials work in
OL,4,CEngland and Wales?
OL,6,FIt is believed cases handled this way
OL,7,Fwill take 20% less time than those
OL,8,Fwith juries.
OL,10,FWhich cases will still face a jury?
OL,12,FAny cases which are likely to carry a
OL,13,Fprison term of at least three years
OL,14,Fwill be heard in front of a jury.
OL,16,FThe most serious and almost all
OL,17,Findictable offences will still face a
OL,18,Fjury, including rape, murder,
OL,19,Faggravated burglary, blackmail, people
OL,20,Ftrafficking, grievous bodily harm and
OL,21,Fthe most serious drug offences.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/18
