OL,3,CHow will no-jury trials work in
OL,4,CEngland and Wales?
OL,6,FCourts to decide where cases are heard
OL,8,FPower will be handed back to courts to
OL,9,Fdecide where cases are heard, which
OL,10,Fministers believe will stop criminals
OL,11,Ffrom being able to "game the system"
OL,12,Fand torment victims.
OL,14,FDefendants in either way cases -
OL,15,Fcriminal offences that can be heard in
OL,16,Fa magistrates' or crown court - will
OL,17,Fno longer be able to choose a jury
OL,18,Ftrial in the crown court if they are
OL,19,Faccused of less serious offences.
OL,21,FMagistrates can increase sentences
