OL,3,CHow will no-jury trials work in
OL,4,CEngland and Wales?
OL,6,FThe right to a jury trial has been
OL,7,Fenshrined in British law since the
OL,8,FMagna Carta in 1215, but ministers
OL,9,Fwarn the already record-breaking
OL,10,Fcourts backlog could rise to 100,000
OL,11,Fby 2028 if nothing is done.
OL,13,FThe government believes the reforms
OL,14,Fwill fast-track around a quarter of
OL,15,Fcases that would otherwise have to
OL,16,Fwait to appear before a jury, freeing
OL,17,Fup jury trials for the most needed
OL,18,Fcases.
OL,20,FWhat has been the response to the
OL,21,Fplans?
