OL,3,CHow will no-jury trials work in
OL,4,CEngland and Wales?
OL,6,FThe plans faced opposition from MPs
OL,7,Fand legal professionals, including
OL,8,Ffrom the Criminal Bar Association and
OL,9,Fthe Bar Council, which argued "there
OL,10,Fis no need to curtail the right to a
OL,11,Ftrial by jury ` from both a principle
OL,12,Fand practical position".
OL,14,FCritics say having 12 people from
OL,15,Fdiffering backgrounds is the best way
OL,16,Fto ensure a fair trial, with some
OL,17,Farguing that restricting trial by jury
OL,18,Fcould negatively impact defendants
OL,19,Ffrom working-class or minority ethnic
OL,20,Fbackgrounds.
