OL,3,CHow will no-jury trials work in
OL,4,CEngland and Wales?
OL,6,FThe Channel Islands have always used
OL,7,Fnon-jury trials, and instead, cases
OL,8,Fare heard by judges or "jurats", known
OL,9,Fas lay judges.
OL,11,FGermany abolished them in 1924 and
OL,12,Fmost cases are tried by a panel made
OL,13,Fup of professional and lay judges,
OL,14,Fwhile the Netherlands have judge-only
OL,15,Ftrials.
